fields.description:
We have multiple themes for our Alloy/Titanium application, and each theme needs to have a different sent of dependencies.

However, dependencies set in app/themes/theme_name/config.json are not checked when returning widget directories:
https://github.com/appcelerator/alloy/blob/5991de44082a492d143612cc2175b7eef30d36e6/Alloy/utils.js#L286

(For reference, this theme config.json _is_ observed when generating the CFG.js file:
https://github.com/appcelerator/alloy/blob/977a2c147e809ccd1c05d197d54828c3e7660150/Alloy/commands/compile/compilerUtils.js#L827)
fields.summary: getWidgetDirectories does not respect theme config.json

comments.body: Hello, Please send a sample code or project for us to test. Also, a guide how to regenerate the issue. Thanks.

I opened a pull request to fix the issue:
https://github.com/appcelerator/alloy/pull/797
[~fmiao] check out the PR and see if it's good for 6.0.0 or better for a future version
